ylas.com%2Fl%2F89c710766f144398ab61e4da539a49cf%2F0%2Fdc4c9e73f2936f3370144e277b2f73b792a6783ba16326b61f21a5c983d7aba9%3Fcache_buster%3D1744637477%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECommon%20Impact%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20an%20organization%20that%20works%20with%20companies%20to%20create%20skills-based%20volunteer%20initiatives%2C%20said%20volunteering%20outside%20a%20workplace%20can%20help%20employees%20grow%20as%20leaders%20and%20develop%20confidence.%20%26quot%3BYou're%20helping%20someone%20else%2C%20you're%20developing%20skills%2C%20you're%20building%20connection%2C%20you're%20being%20connected%20to%20the%20outside%20world%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%20%26quot%3BSometimes%2C%20you're%20just%20validating%20the%20skills%20you%20already%20have%20that%20you%20don't%20realize%20are%20so%20valuable%20to%20someone%20else.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Hutchisson%20said%20if%20an%20employee%20is%20in%20an%20early-career%20finance%20role%20and%20wants%20to%20be%20a%20CFO%2C%20they%20could%20grow%20their%20skillset%20by%20helping%20a%20nonprofit%20prepare%20for%20an%20audit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBlue%20Cross%20Blue%20Shield%20of%20Massachusetts%20works%20with%20Common%20Impact%2C%20a%20nonprofit%20organization%2C%20to%20design%20skills-based%20volunteer%20programs.%20Lucy%20Darragh%2C%20the%20director%20of%20strategy%20and%20social%20impact%20at%20Blue%20Cross%20Blue%20Shield%20of%20Massachusetts%2C%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20Common%20Impact%20provides%20guidance%20on%20how%20to%20design%20a%20program%20that%20strategically%20meets%20the%20needs%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fai-career-coach-accessible-employee-coaching-professional-development-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edevelopment%3C%2Fa%3E%20and%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Femployee-wellbeing-programs-help-companies-perform-better-and-manage-cost-2024-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eengagement%3C%2Fa%3E%20while%20also%20benefiting%20the%20nonprofit.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20partnership%20led%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcareers.bluecrossma.org%2Fus%2Fen%2Fcorporate-citizenship%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EBCBS%3C%2Fa%3E%20to%20offer%20two%20distinct%20opportunities%3A%20a%20short-term%20consulting%20engagement%20and%20an%20advisory%20partnership%20that%20lasts%20several%20months.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20the%20limited-time%20volunteer%20opportunity%2C%20a%20team%20of%20four%20or%20five%20associates%20will%20work%20with%20a%20nonprofit%20on%20a%20specific%20project%20for%20three%20weeks%2C%20providing%20a%20final%20deliverable%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%20program.%20%26quot%3BWe%20help%20scope%20a%20project%20that%20we%20think%20can%20be%20achieved%20in%20three%20weeks%2C%20then%20we%20recruit%20a%20team%20of%20people%2C%20typically%20folks%20who%20don't%20work%20together%2C%26quot%3B%20Darragh%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20long-term%20advisory%20engagement%20is%20similar%2C%20but%20the%20timeline%20for%20the%20work%20is%20more%20spread%20out.%20In%20some%20cases%2C%20the%20advisory%20engagement%20will%20build%20on%20the%20short-term%20consulting%20project.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EDarragh%20said%20skills-based%20volunteering%20provides%20a%20meaningful%20way%20for%20employees%20to%20showcase%20the%20skills%20they%20use%20in%20an%20office%20and%20to%20see%20how%20those%20talents%20could%20translate%20into%20a%20different%20environment.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20also%20provides%20this%20special%20layer%20of%20networking%2C%20teamwork%2C%20and%20connections%20that%20we%20need%20to%20intentionally%20cultivate%20in%20our%20hybrid%20work%20environment%20with%20folks%20across%20our%20organization%2C%26quot%3B%20she%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAt%20Ares%2C%20many%20young%20professionals%20have%20participated%20in%20the%20company's%20skills-based%20volunteer%20program.%20Fabiaschi%20said%20she's%20noticed%20that%20junior%20colleagues%20return%20to%20work%20with%20increased%20confidence%20after%20volunteering.%20She%20added%20that%20the%20experience%20has%20also%20created%20a%20sense%20of%20camaraderie%20among%20employees%20who%20work%20on%20the%20same%20projects.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAres%20recently%20launched%20its%202025%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.aresmgmt.com%2Fabout-ares-management-corporation%2Fwho-we-are%2Fcommunity-involvement%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESummer%20of%20Service%3C%2Fa%3E%20with%2060%20global%20volunteer%20events.%20The%20firm%20said%20it's%20expected%20to%20engage%20up%20to%201%2C100%20volunteers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%224789%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Lucy%20Darragh%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F6848751685e81483682bcec7%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223592%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3ELucy%20Darragh%20is%20the%20director%20of%20strategy%20and%20social%20impact%20at%20Blue%20Cross%20Blue%20Shield.%3Cp%3ECourtesy%20of%20Blue%20Cross%20Blue%20Shield%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%226a33f7ef-b0d5-497f-804f-06557a6abbc8%5C%22%3EHow%20to%20build%20volunteer%20opportunities%20at%20work%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20companies%20looking%20to%20start%20a%20skills-based%20volunteer%20program%2C%20Fabiaschi%20suggests%20starting%20small%20and%20giving%20employees%20%26quot%3Bchoice%20and%20voice.%26quot%3B%20She%20said%20companies%20should%20first%20establish%20an%20employee-led%20committee%20to%20find%20out%20which%20type%20of%20volunteering%20garners%20the%20most%20interest.%20Then%2C%20she%20added%2C%20the%20group%20should%20organize%20a%20set%20day%20or%20week%20of%20service.%20For%20example%2C%20a%20company%20could%20schedule%20one%20day%20a%20week%20at%20a%20soup%20kitchen%20or%20a%20firm-wide%20park%20cleanup.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20year%2C%20Ares%20added%20a%20new%20volunteer%20opportunity%20around%20Financial%20Literacy%20Month.%20%26quot%3BWe%20have%20a%20whole%20bench%20of%20talent%20with%20financial%20literacy%20expertis